[SN]TITLE[SN]
Scott Harrison: Hartlepool United defender signs new deal at Victoria Park

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Hartlepool United have handed defender Scott Harrison a new contract, although terms remain undisclosed.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Harrison, 23, was re-signed by Pools in August last year, after he was initially released in May 2016 having made 70 appearances.
Since rejoining the club he has made 33 appearances, scoring once, and has started the past 18 League Two games.
He first moved to Victoria Park in February 2015 after a loan spell at Pools from parent club Sunderland.
